1
00:00:30,333 --> 00:00:32,333
[CHOIR SINGING DIRGE]

2
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:53,580
[DIRGE CONTINUES]

3
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,383
[ORGANA] You shouldn't have come here.

4
00:01:22,166 --> 00:01:24,166
There's nothing you could have done.

5
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:26,543
For either of them.

6
00:01:30,458 --> 00:01:31,458
Why risk it?

7
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:42,208
She was my friend.

8
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:48,330
[COMMS CHATTER IN DISTANCE]

9
00:01:48,416 --> 00:01:49,416
There's a patrol coming.

10
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:51,290
You must leave.

11
00:01:51,375 --> 00:01:53,325
- Where is your ship?
- The river.

12
00:01:53,416 --> 00:01:54,626
This way.

13
00:02:00,291 --> 00:02:02,461
[COMMS CHATTER]

14
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:14,040
Here.

15
00:02:15,583 --> 00:02:18,133
If you need anything,
you can contact me with this.

16
00:02:20,916 --> 00:02:21,916
No.

17
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:25,788
I'm tired of fighting.

18
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:28,633
[COMMS CHATTER]

19
00:02:28,708 --> 00:02:30,208
[SECURITY CLONE] You there!

20
00:02:34,291 --> 00:02:36,291
What can I do for you, officer?

21
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:38,625
[SECURITY CLONE]
Let's see some identification.

22
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:40,125
Of course.

23
00:02:43,791 --> 00:02:46,581
[SECURITY CLONE]
Senator Organa of Alderaan.

24
00:02:46,666 --> 00:02:47,666
[ORGANA] That's right.

25
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,920
I'm afraid no one
is allowed back here, Senator.

26
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,080
Imperial orders.

27
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:55,626
Forgive me. It's easy to get lost
with all that has happened.

28
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:59,290
Still, we have a duty. Don't we?

29
00:03:00,291 --> 00:03:01,671
An obligation to uphold,

30
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:04,498
when we're able.

31
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:09,633
We'll have to escort you back
to the procession, Senator.

32
00:03:09,708 --> 00:03:10,708
I understand.

33
00:03:11,458 --> 00:03:16,168
And if you should ever need anything,
please contact me.

34
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:49,416
[ENGINES POWERING UP]

35
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,213
[DROID BEEPING]

36
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:49,745
[VILLAGE SISTER] You just leave me to it.

37
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:52,583
This is my payload, not yours!

38
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:56,166
I'm just telling you, you gotta hurry up.
We're gonna break for lunch.

39
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:59,496
[RUMBLING]

40
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:04,503
You're piling them up too high. Again.

41
00:05:04,583 --> 00:05:06,043
I know what I'm doing.

42
00:05:06,125 --> 00:05:08,955
[BELL CHIMING]

43
00:05:09,541 --> 00:05:12,081
Break time. Break time.

44
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:16,456
Hey, droid. Finish up!

45
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,420
- You can't leave it like that.
- I'm hungry!

46
00:05:21,416 --> 00:05:22,876
[DROID BEEPS]

47
00:05:27,666 --> 00:05:29,956
[SHRIEKS, BEEPS]

48
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,710
Lucky.

49
00:05:56,791 --> 00:05:58,831
Very lucky, child.

50
00:06:08,125 --> 00:06:09,705
[DROID BEEPS]

51
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:13,503
[DROID WHIRRING, BEEPING]

52
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:28,915
Ashla, come sit with us.

53
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,000
Please?

54
00:06:44,958 --> 00:06:48,458
No one can keep up
with the Imperial quotas.

55
00:06:48,541 --> 00:06:51,131
It gets more difficult every season.

56
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:53,918
In the beginning,
you all welcomed the Empire.

57
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Not as warmly as you.

58
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,708
Emperor Palpatine brought peace.

59
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:02,333
Through persecution.

60
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:06,376
Not citizens like us!
Only rebels who threatened the Empire.

61
00:07:07,541 --> 00:07:09,081
No one is safe.

62
00:07:09,916 --> 00:07:10,996
Only if you aren't loyal.

63
00:07:12,458 --> 00:07:13,878
We are safe.

64
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,668
But not because of the Empire.

65
00:07:32,291 --> 00:07:33,671
[DROID BEEPING]

66
00:07:34,375 --> 00:07:37,575
Don't forget, we have to take the harvest
over to Mon-Hella tomorrow.

67
00:07:37,666 --> 00:07:41,076
That path can be dangerous.
Is your brother coming along?

68
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:44,746
No. But we'll be fine, won't we?

69
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:46,666
[WHISPERING] Master Jedi.

70
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:50,041
You shouldn't say such things.

71
00:07:50,125 --> 00:07:52,745
I saw you push the bales clear of me.

72
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:54,963
You have it wrong.

73
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:57,131
Why didn't you tell us?

74
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:58,668
There's nothing to tell.

75
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:02,918
[WHISPERING] Don't worry. It's our secret.

76
00:08:03,666 --> 00:08:06,166
I'll meet you near the field.
At first light!

77
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:30,958
[DROID CHIRPING]

78
00:08:33,791 --> 00:08:36,921
Now, remember, don't accept
the first price they offer you.

79
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,920
- I know. Haggle.
- [DROID BEEPS]

80
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,210
Don't worry.

81
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:42,375
See you tomorrow.

82
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,580
May the Force be with you.

83
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:09,498
[DROID BEEPS]

84
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:13,003
Prices were so low,
they're bleeding us dry.

85
00:09:13,083 --> 00:09:15,583
I couldn't get half
of what they offered us last season.

86
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:30,125
[DROID WHIRRING]

87
00:09:33,291 --> 00:09:35,251
[BEEPS, WHIMPERS]

88
00:09:53,708 --> 00:09:59,918
You claim a Jedi was here,
and yet, I find no one.

89
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,380
I promise you.
They'll be back. I turned her in.

90
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:05,625
I-I should be rewarded.

91
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:11,420
You lie to me and expect Imperial favor?

92
00:10:12,041 --> 00:10:13,331
[AHSOKA] He's not lying.

93
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:25,878
And who might you be?

94
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,830
Let them go.

95
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:30,576
- She's the Jedi!
- Stop it!

96
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:32,746
See. I told you they'd be back.

97
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:35,955
So you did.

98
00:10:38,541 --> 00:10:40,131
Here is your reward.

99
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:41,710
No!

100
00:10:42,916 --> 00:10:43,916
[GRUNTS]

101
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:57,828
Can it be?

102
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:08,421
You're supposed to be dead.

103
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:25,211
Looks like I shall be rewarded...

104
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:30,286
Ahsoka Tano!

105
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:40,206
[GRUNTS]

106
00:11:40,291 --> 00:11:41,751
[SCREECHES]

107
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:55,420
Look! Look what you did.

108
00:11:56,708 --> 00:11:57,918
Look what you did!

109
00:11:58,708 --> 00:11:59,788
I'm sorry.

110
00:12:00,916 --> 00:12:02,376
I'm so sorry.

111
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,000
I know.

112
00:12:05,166 --> 00:12:06,246
More will come.

113
00:12:07,666 --> 00:12:11,956
- You're going to have to leave.
- How? Where?

114
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:27,628
[SHIP APPROACHING]

115
00:12:27,708 --> 00:12:31,128
[ENGINES ROARING]

116
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,130
- [HATCH OPENS]
- [BOARDING CHAMBER LOWERS]

117
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,380
Please, this way.

118
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:01,460
I was beginning to think you lost this.

119
00:13:03,458 --> 00:13:05,998
Things have only gotten worse.

120
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:10,996
Are you sure you are ready
to get back into the fight?

